-The build failed because many files installed during `%install` are not listed in the `%files` section. This is a classic "unpacked files" error — the `check-files` RPM post-install hook rejected the package.
-
-## Root Cause
-
-The `%files` section of the spec file is missing entries for:
-- **Profile scripts**: `/etc/profile.d/gawk.csh`, `/etc/profile.d/gawk.sh`
-- **Additional binaries**: `/usr/bin/gawk-5.4.0`, `/usr/bin/gawkbug`
-- **Header**: `/usr/include/gawkapi.h`
-- **Debug files** in `/usr/lib/debug/...` (these are auto-generated and typically handled by `%debuginfo`)
-- **Dynamic extensions**: all `.so` and `.a` files in `/usr/lib64/gawk/`
-- **Helper binaries**: `/usr/libexec/awk/grcat`, `pwcat`
-- **AWK standard library scripts**: all `.awk` files under `/usr/share/awk/`
-- **Info documentation**: PNG figures, `.info.gz` files
-- **Locale files**: all `*.mo` in `/usr/share/locale/*/LC_MESSAGES/gawk.mo`
-- **Additional man pages**: `gawkbug.1`, `pm-gawk.1`, and the extension man pages (`.3am.gz`)
-
-## Fix
-
-Add the missing patterns to the `%files` section of the spec file. Here's what needs to be added:
-
-```spec
-%files
-%defattr(-, root, root)
-/usr/bin/gawk*
-/usr/bin/ptx
-%{gawklibdir}/*.{so,a}
-%{_includedir}/gawkapi.h
-/etc/profile.d/gawk.sh
-/etc/profile.d/gawk.csh
-%dir %{_libexecdir}/awk
-%{_libexecdir}/awk/grcat
-%{_libexecdir}/awk/pwcat
-%{gawkincludedir}/*
-%dir %{_datadir}/gawk
-%{_datadir}/gawk/*.awk
-%if 0%{?suse_version} >= 13250
-%license COPYING
-%doc ChangeLog README NEWS TODO
-%else
-%doc COPYING ChangeLog README NEWS TODO
-%endif
-%lang(ar) %{_datadir}/locale/ar/LC_MESSAGES/gawk.mo
-# ... (or more concisely:)
-%{_datadir}/locale/*/LC_MESSAGES/gawk.mo
-%ifarch x86_64 i586
-%doc %{_infodir}/gawk_api_figure*.png
-%doc %{_infodir}/gawk_array_elements.png
-%doc %{_infodir}/gawk_general_program.png
-%doc %{_infodir}/gawk_process_flow.png
-%doc %{_infodir}/gawk_statistics.jpg
-%{_infodir}/gawkinet.info.gz
-%{_infodir}/gawkworkflow.info.gz
-%{_infodir}/notes.info.gz
-%{_infodir}/pm-gawk.info.gz
-%endif
-%{?suse_update_doc:%suse_update_doc -e 0}
-```
-
-The debug files in `/usr/lib/debug/` are typically handled by the `%debuginfo` subpackage automatically — if they're not being caught, you may need to add a `gawk-debuginfo` subpackage or ensure `%debug_package` is invoked properly. The `.3am.gz` man pages can be added with `%{_mandir}/man3/filefuncs.3am.gz %{_mandir}/man3/fnmatch.3am.gz ...` (listing them individually) or by using a glob if the directory structure allows it.
-
-After editing the spec file, rebuild with:
-```bash
-rpmbuild -bb ~/rpmbuild/SOURCES/gawk.spec
-```
